<plot>In this promotional short for _Patch of Blue, A (1965)_ (qv), director 'Guy Green (I)' (qv) describes how and why 'Elizabeth Hartman (I)' (qv) was chosen for the leading role in her first picture. We see an interview and screen test. After she has been chosen, Elizabeth visits the Braille Institute of America in Los Angeles, where she sees how blind people are taught everyday tasks, such as opening drawers, and threading a needle.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?008592</url></doc>
